issue.title: feat: consolidate infrastructure images into dedicated workflow
issue.body:
## Summary

Consolidates all infrastructure images (PostgreSQL+pgvector, rust-builder, runtime) into a dedicated workflow, separating them from AI agents for better organization and maintainability.

## Key Changes

### üèóÔ∏è **New Infrastructure Workflow**
- **Created**  - Dedicated workflow for infrastructure images
- **Unified scheduling** at 7 AM UTC (after agents at 6 AM) 
- **Matrix-based building** with selective image support
- **Smart runner cycling** when rust-builder updates

### üîÑ **Workflow Consolidation**
- **Moved rust-builder** from  to infrastructure workflow
- **Added PostgreSQL+pgvector** with high-dimensional vector support (3072-dim)
- **Deprecated**  with clear migration instructions
- **Enhanced** selective building via workflow_dispatch parameters

### üì¶ **Infrastructure Images**
- ‚úÖ **PostgreSQL+pgvector**: Bitnami PostgreSQL 16 + pgvector for text-embedding-3-large
- ‚úÖ **rust-builder**: Pre-warmed Rust development environment for CI/CD  
- ‚úÖ **runtime**: Base image with development tools and dependencies
- ‚úÖ **Clean naming**: All use  scheme

## Architecture

### **Workflow Separation**


### **Smart Features**
- **üéõÔ∏è Selective Building**: 
- **ÔøΩÔøΩ Auto Runner Cycling**: Restarts Arc runners when rust-builder updates
- **üìä Rich Summaries**: Detailed build reports and GHCR integration
- **‚ö° Optimized Scheduling**: Avoids conflicts with logical timing

## Benefits

- üéØ **Perfect Separation of Concerns** - Agents vs Infrastructure clearly divided
- üèóÔ∏è **Unified Infrastructure Management** - All infrastructure in one workflow
- üì¶ **PostgreSQL Consolidation** - Removes external repo dependency
- ‚ö° **Enhanced Productivity** - Rust dev environment with pre-warmed dependencies
- üîß **Better Maintainability** - Logical grouping and clear migration paths

## Testing

- [x] Infrastructure workflow builds successfully
- [x] PostgreSQL image supports 3072-dimensional vectors  
- [x] rust-builder image works with Arc runners
- [x] Selective building via workflow_dispatch
- [x] Proper deprecation notices and migration guidance

Ready for AgentDocs cleanup and improved CI/CD workflows! üöÄ

Update packaging script to support ARM64 properly.

Fix SDL multiwindow freezing in some cases on macOS

Need SDL_HINT_MAC_OPENGL_ASYNC_DISPATCH set, apparently.

Move some swapping code behind #ifdef

idk I just did this while debugging something and there's no harm committing it.
Avoid WinBlit threads getting stuck forever when their window closes.
Fix secondary window closing breaking rendering on macOS

Disable threaded window blit on macOS

Can probably do this on Linux too, but I didn't test that.

This feature is, fundamentally, a workaround to avoid WGL MakeCurrent() constantly breaking. The extra threading complexity is not a good thing on other platforms, so get rid of it.

Package FreeBSD by default.

We won't officially support FreeBSD launcher builds, but this at least allows third-party launcher builds to have an engine to load properly.

Make SDL3 file dialogs have parent window.

Somehow needed to avoid causing it to block on macOS.

Fix TextInputSetRect not accounting for pixel ratio properly.

commits.message:
feat: add branches and checkout commands

Add a 'g' group for git commands to the application, within this
there are two new commands: branches, and co.

The branches command shows the branches available in the current
repository, and optionally searches them. It has an option to
enable/disable fuzzy searching which is based on an external library
using levenshtein distance.

The co command uses the same logic as above, you can enter a branch
name that you'd like to checkout and it will search branches for a
match. If there is only one match, it will just check it out. If
there are multiple matches, then it will present an interactive
choice where you can use the TUI to select which branch you actually
want.

To implement the choices TUI, I used the bubbletea package. This
handles the interactivity for the app.

To implement the git commands, it is using the exec package, but i
introduced a service within the hostsys package to abstract this a
bit and avoid some duplication each time we need to call execute a
tool in the system.

While doing this I also introduced a logging package that we can use
to configure log levels throughout the app. As most of this is a
kind of TUI, the errors are presented anyway so the log level by
default is a custom "none" level that won't show anything. This log
level is a persistent flag that can be changed on each command and
will show more errors if needed for debugging.

pull_request.title: Implement FantasyLife parser output transformations
pull_request.body:
This PR implements three specific output transformations for the FantasyLife parser to standardize the data format:

## Changes Made

1. **Column Renaming**: `'#'` column is renamed to `'Jersey_Number'`
2. **Percentage Conversion**: `'Comp%'` values are converted from percentage strings (e.g., `'69%'`) to decimal format (e.g., `0.69`)
3. **Numeric Conversion**: `'P Yds'` values are converted from comma-separated strings (e.g., `'3,735.5'`) to numeric format (e.g., `3735.5`)

## Before
```python
{'#': 4,
 'Player': 'Jayden Daniels',
 'Position': 'QB',
 'Team': 'WAS',
 'P Att': 497.0,
 'Comp': 339.5,
 'Comp%': '69%',
 'P Yds': '3,735.5',
 'TD': 25.4,
 'Int': 9.6,
 'R Att': 138.9,
 'Ru Yds': 816.1,
 'Ru TD': 5.5,
 'Proj': 356.1}
```

## After
```python
{'Jersey_Number': 4,
 'Player': 'Jayden Daniels',
 'Position': 'QB',
 'Team': 'WAS',
 'P Att': 497.0,
 'Comp': 339.5,
 'Comp%': 0.69,
 'P Yds': 3735.5,
 'TD': 25.4,
 'Int': 9.6,
 'R Att': 138.9,
 'Ru Yds': 816.1,
 'Ru TD': 5.5,
 'Proj': 356.1}
```

## Implementation Details

- Added a new `_transform_record()` method that handles transformations in-place
- Robust error handling for invalid data (gracefully handles non-conforming values)
- Backward compatibility maintained - data without these columns continues to work unchanged
- All existing tests pass, plus new tests added to validate the transformations

Fixes #54.
